					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">HJRodrigo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Wow, I did not know that. Looks like it is nearly identical to a NTSC signal other than the encoding of the colour carrier. So it can technically work on NTSC TVs, but the picture will be in black and white.</div><br />Yes, you can mix PAL-M and NTSC devices and only lose the color. Many consoles released in Brazil were basically NTSC units, with added parts to handle the color conversion. The NES and the Atari 2600 are examples of consoles that can easily be converted back to NTSC if you simply change the oscillator and remove an add-on board.</div>

