					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A DVI-I input can receive both DVI-D signals (electrically the same as HDMI) and DVI-A signals (electrically the same as VGA). A DVI to HDMI cable works only with DVI-D signals, not DVI-A signals. This means a couple of my PCs, which have only VGA outputs, are completely incompatible. A converter from VGA (or DVI-A) to HDMI (or DVI-D) would need an ADC.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

